name: rank_filter
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "rank_filter" %}
{% set version = "0.4.11" %}
{% set checksum = "246f5c73ebd03314d9b2cff3ede74330" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  md5: {{ checksum }}

build:
  skip: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - boost >=1.56
    - python
    - setuptools >=18.0
    - numpy x.x
    - numpy >=1.7
    - cython >=0.23

  run:
    - boost >=1.56
    - python
    - numpy x.x
    - numpy >=1.7

test:
  imports:
    - rank_filter

about:
  home: https://github.com/nanshe-org/rank_filter
  license: BSD 3-Clause
  summary: 'A simple python module containing an in-place linear rank filter optimized in C++.'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jakirkham
